# Linting Standards

## Tools

| Language | Tool | Config |
|----------|------|--------|
| Python | Ruff (lint + format) | `pyproject.toml` |
| JS/TS/TSX | ESLint 9 | `apps/frontend/eslint.config.js` |

## When to Lint

- **Before every commit** — `./scripts/lint.sh --staged` (enforced by pre-commit hook)
- **Before every push** — `./scripts/lint.sh` (enforced by pre-push hook)
- **Before generating commit messages** — agent runs lint first
- **After editing Python or frontend files** — fix lint errors before marking work complete

## Commands

```bash
./scripts/lint.sh              # full lint
./scripts/lint.sh --staged     # staged files only
./scripts/lint.sh --fix        # auto-fix
./scripts/lint.sh --python     # ruff only
./scripts/lint.sh --js         # eslint only
```

## Setup (one-time)

```bash
chmod +x scripts/lint.sh scripts/setup-githooks.sh
./scripts/setup-githooks.sh    # install pre-commit + pre-push hooks
pip install ruff               # or via apps/backend/requirements-dev.txt
cd apps/frontend && npm install
```

## Agent Skills

- `ruff-lint` — Python linting workflow
- `eslint-check` — Frontend linting workflow
- `git-commit-messages` — requires lint pass before generating message
